OL,3,C'Little privacy or dignity for
OL,4,Cpatients': An emergency department
OL,5,Cunder strain
OL,7,FPatients located near the doors to
OL,8,Fresus were witness to critically-ill
OL,9,Fpatients.
OL,11,FKathryn Whithorn described the
OL,12,Femergency department as "absolutely
OL,13,Fmad".
OL,15,F"I can't go anywhere because I'm on
OL,16,Foxygen.
OL,18,F"You can't get the lights turned down
OL,19,Fto go to sleep, so it's always the
OL,20,Fsame brightness.
